It stores values that are unique and in a sorted order.
Syntax :
set<int>s;
Insertion :
s.insert(12);
Traversal :
for(int i :s){
cout<<i<<" ";
}
Searching :
if(s.find(12)!=s.end()){
cout<<"Found"<<endl;
}
vector
↓
Can contain duplicates
Keeps insertion order

set
↓
No duplicates
Always sorted

unordered_set
↓
No duplicates
Fastest lookup
No order

multiset
↓
Duplicates allowed
Always sorted
